<h2 id="what-is-an-inverted-pc-case">What is an Inverted PC Case?</h2>

<p>An inverted PC case is exactly what it sounds like - rather than a traditional motherboard configuration, the motherboard is inverted so that the GPU is on top and the CPU is on bottom.</p>

<p><img class="lazyload" alt="inverted PC case example" src="/img/cases/inverted/inverted.png" /></p>

<p>In addition, inverted PC cases have their side panel window on the right side, which is great for those that can only fit their case on the left side of their desk.</p>

<p>Although this video is a few years old and the 600C is no longer on the market, it does a great job talking about inverted PC cases in general:</p>

